description._content: Description: Big Aleppo Pine - Pinus Halepensis about 80 years old, with other smaller Aleppo Pines at the back and Arbutus - Arbutus Andrachne in the foreground, Troodos Forest, Elevation 3,500 feet above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: Portion of the Platres - Mesa Potamos Forest Road, showing also Aleppo Pine - Pinus halepensis, 60 years old, Elevation 3,400 feet above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
